TextAsset.value: Huh. It was pretty easy to sneak out of detention…
Of course it’s easy for a pair of super sleuths like us!
...I was gonna say…
Almost TOO easy.
Oh, nonsense. Don’t worry too much!
I brought disguises for us both, in case someone were to discover us roaming the halls when we shouldn’t.
Here you are! ;B
(Fake… mustaches…)
I don’t know if I feel comfortable wearing this in front of you now…
Ahahaha! Ha. Ha…
Sh-shut up!
So where are we going anyway?
Hoo hoo hoo! That would be telling!
Uh, yeah!
That’s what I’m asking you to do.
Well, I can maybe give you a little hint.
I asked a friend of mine to meet us in the library, which should be empty at this hour…
Well, as long as we don’t run into the hall monitor, we should be fine.
H-halt, students!
Shouldn’t you be in detention?
Oh no…
Hmm? What is it?
There’s Meowkie…
the hall monitor…
Oh pish posh. It’s that silly “talking” cat again.
Perhaps it’s a puppet of some kind…?
I think Davesprite knows a thing or two about puppets…
E-excuse me?!
HALT, CITIZENS! You should be in detention!
Omigosh! Who is that amazing superhero?!
I’ve never seen her around the school before!
Superhero? Come on, ${slot:playerName}. Do you have a pumpkin for a brain?
It’s obviously just a ridiculous costume.
R-Rude…!
I know, right!
Jane, aren’t you at least worried that we’ve been caught?!
We’re gonna be in SO much trouble…
Oh, please!
We can take ‘em ;B
ROOOOAAARRRR!
GAH!
Don’t tell me you think we can take HIM…?
Sure, he’s just a normal guy in a mask after all!
Roar?!
(How can anyone look at that guy and think “normal”...)
Not to worry, ${slot:playerName}.
I may look like a bespectacled nerdy girl…
But I can certainly hold my own in a fight!
Watch and learn :B
I don’t think fighting a teacher is such a good idea…
(Whoah! She just pulled out … what looks like a giant red spoon?!
Where did that come from? Did she just pull it from nowhere?!
What on Earth is going on with this girl?!)
Strife specibus… SPOONKIND!
Aggress!!!
(She’s grabbing my hand and running towards the others…
I wish she wouldn’t drag me into her death wish!)
S-stop!
Halt!
ROAR!
AUGH!
Hoo! :B
(She’s just sweeping them aside with her big red spoon thing…
I still don’t know where the heck that came from!
Or how she can use it so effectively as a weapon!)
Have at you!
Nyaa-!
Argh!
Roar…
(I can’t watch…
Omigosh, she actually made it past them??
And she’s still running…
Looks like… we’re actually in the clear now..)
Hoo hoo! Nothing like a skirmish to get the blood pumping, huh?
How are you doing, ${slot:playerName}? Are you alright?
Jane… that was amazing!
But… I don’t understand at all!
What was that giant spoon thing?!
How did you fight with it so well?
Where is it now?! That thing was huge…
You couldn’t have just put it in your pocket!
Huh? I’ve had that thing for forever…
It’s not anything special.
I just captchalogued it. Are you quite sure you’re alright?
Whaa…?
Don’t you have a fetch modus or anything? :|
Why are you talking silly talk.
Use real words.
Maybe they call it something different where you’re from…
How can you deny that anything weird is going on in this school?!
Especially now!
You’re like… the weirdest person I’ve ever met!
Hey now! Shut up!
There’s no call for language like that.
I’ve been listening to you jabber on and on about how “strange things” are going on…
Just because you refuse to use your brain and think about how implausible those things really are!
And now, you call ME weird, just because I use a technology you’re unfamiliar with?!
I try to keep my temper under control, but ${slot:playerName}, really…
How would you feel if I called YOU weird?!
But Jane…
I AM WEIRD!!!
I’m a little cousin of the Prince of All Cosmos…
I roll things up into stars and planets…
And I come from space!
See my antenna and my space suit thing?!
I wouldn’t mind being called weird!
Nonsense, ${slot:playerName}!
It’s futile to try to trick me. I have the sharp eye of a master investigator, you know!
It’s obvious that if I were to take that space suit off you, you’d just look like a normal human!
...Um! Not like that!
Er, nevermind!
Just forget I said anything!
HOO HOO! (Stupid, stupid…)
H3Y J4N3
YOU 4SK3D M3 TO M33T YOU 1N TH3 L1BR4RY?
WH4T’S UP
A-HA! Perfect timing, Terezi!
See, ${slot:playerName}! Now I’ll prove to you how silly all your little delusions are!
Every single person at this school is just as normal as you or I…
Even my old chum Terezi!
WHO4H, WH4T…
YAH!
(OH MY GOSH! Jane just jumped on top on Terezi!
I think… I think she’s trying to yank her horns off??)
Hmm, these are being awfully stubborn…
Must be some kind of… intensely strong…
Cosplay… glue?!
H-H3Y! G3T OFF!
1 DON’T L1K3 TO F1GHT MY FR13NDS…
BUT YOU L34V3 M3 NO CHO1C3!
(Whoah! That cane Terezi uses…
It’s also a sword?!
That’s gotta be against school rules…)
GAH! Honestly…
(Wow! Jane blocked Terezi’s sword-cane with her giant spoon…
Seriously, where does that thing keep coming from?!
Now they’re sparring with their weapons…
It looks like fighting to this is as natural to them as breathing…
This is kind of awesome…
But also… SCARY!!!
Please, someone come stop this…
Please!)
ROOOARRR!
H-he says “You’re all in big trouble!”
(...Be careful what you wish for.)
(So we all got in big trouble.
Terezi’s in there with Principal Dig Dug now, explaining what happened…
King said Jane and I have double detention now.
Whatever that means..)
...Maybe it’s a full-body suit with the hair and horns attached?
That would explain why pulling on the horns wouldn’t loosen them.
It would also explain why the gray bodypaint doesn’t get rubbed off from time to time!
Seriously?!
You STILL don’t think anything’s abnormal?!
You fought one of your friends with a SWORD today!
What’s abnormal about that…?
Don’t be ridiculous.
AUGH! You are the most frustrating person I’ve ever met…
I’m sorry…
I’m not trying to frustrate anyone. :|
I’m just trying to show you what’s what.
But… I already feel like I know what’s what.
Can’t you trust what I have to say?
...I’m not going to change what I think just because you tell me you see things differently.
(...I guess that’s fair.)
In any case…
I’m sorry we got in trouble, but…
I’m glad you came with me today.
I hope, er… Well, that is…
This sort of thing is hard for me to say…
I hope you, um… had fun too?
At least a little bit…
Are you kidding?
Of course I did.
You’re a good friend, ${slot:playerName}. :B
